<p><a name="Fictional_Spin_Doctors" id="Fictional_Spin_Doctors"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Spin_(public_relations)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Fictional Spin Doctors">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Fictional Spin Doctors</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Nick_Naylor" title="Nick Naylor" class="mw-redirect">Nick Naylor</a> - Protagonist of <a href="/wiki/Christopher_Buckley" title="Christopher Buckley">Christopher Buckley</a>'s bestseller <i><a href="/wiki/Thank_You_for_Smoking_(novel)" title="Thank You for Smoking (novel)">Thank You for Smoking</a></i>.</li>
<li>Deputy Mayor <a href="/wiki/Mike_Flaherty" title="Mike Flaherty" class="mw-redirect">Mike Flaherty</a> in the American <a href="/wiki/Sitcom" title="Sitcom" class="mw-redirect">sitcom</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Spin_City" title="Spin City">Spin City</a>.</i></li>
<li>Malcolm Tucker - enforcer from Number 10 in the BBC comedy <i><a href="/wiki/The_Thick_of_It" title="The Thick of It">The Thick of It</a>.</i></li>
<li>Conrad Brean - hired to save a presidential election in <i><a href="/wiki/Wag_the_Dog" title="Wag the Dog">Wag the Dog</a>.</i></li>
<li>Charles Prentiss and Martin McCabe in the BBC comedy <i><a href="/wiki/Absolute_Power_(comedy)" title="Absolute Power (comedy)">Absolute Power</a></i>.</li>
</ul>
